<h1>Problem 886 - 2020 IMOSL, G4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>In the plane, there are \(n \geqslant 6\) pairwise disjoint disks \(D_{1}, D_{2}, \ldots, D_{n}\) with radii \(R_{1} \geqslant R_{2} \geqslant \ldots \geqslant R_{n}\). For every \(i=1,2, \ldots, n\), a point \(P_{i}\) is chosen in disk \(D_{i} .\) Let \(O\) be an arbitrary point in the plane. Prove that
\[O P_{1}+O P_{2}+\ldots+O P_{n} \geqslant R_{6}+R_{7}+\ldots+R_{n}\]
(A disk is assumed to contain its boundary.)</p>
